mousePointer.e:

  newPointer(pointerImage) - Create and initialize a mouse pointer.  Allocates
        chip memory and initializes a mouse pointer image from image data.
        pointerImage is a pointer to an array of integers; must be longword
        aligned, and must be 16x16 pixels, even if some of the pixels aren't
        used.  No sanity checks are made.  Returns a pointer to the new mouse
        pointer image, or NIL if unsuccessful.

  freePointer(pointer) - free the chip memory at location pointer.  NOTE:  MUST
        be called in order to free the pointer; CleanUp()  !!! WILL NOT !!!
        return the memory.

  setPointer(win,pointer) - set pointer for window win.

